    <item>
      <title>Ideaya/Servier - Uveal Melanoma Drug (Darovasertib)</title>
      <link>https://www.google.com</link>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Summary:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Darovasertib&lt;/b&gt;, a uveal melanoma drug from &lt;b&gt;Ideaya&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;Servier&lt;/b&gt;, exceeds success benchmarks in a late-stage trial, demonstrating best-in-class efficacy and paving the way for an FDA submission. The drug shows clear promise in treating this rare eye cancer.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;MoAs:&lt;/b&gt; Darovasertib is a protein kinase C (PKC) inhibitor, targeting the PKC pathway involved in uveal melanoma cell proliferation and survival.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sources:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.oncologypipeline.com/apexonco/ideayas-darovasertib-plan-comes-together"&gt;ApexOnco&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.biospace.com/drug-development/ideaya-and-serviers-eye-cancer-drug-heads-to-fda-after-delivering-best-in-class-efficacy"&gt;BioSpace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.fiercebiotech.com/biotech/ideaya-sees-clear-path-fda-servier-partnered-eye-cancer-drug-hits-goal"&gt;Fierce Biotech&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://endpoints.news/ideayas-uveal-melanoma-drug-exceeds-success-benchmark-in-late-stage-trial/"&gt;Endpoints News&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
